value.0: "Ah, I see you're back again... no wait, that's your front, ha, ha, ha! Sorry, old jokes die hard. So what can I do for you?"
"I know that it should actually be more than this, but you have done well by us here in the keep. I'm only charging you an extra ten gold."
"No problem. Come back any time and pay me. I'll keep your bill on hand."
"Well, I do have staff to pay, otherwise I'd agree. Ten gold is not so much, in the scheme of things."
"You be welcome here at the Mossy Tree, any time you be wanting to visit."
"Thank you very much, <master/mistress>. I am pleased that you chose to stay with us here at the Mossy Tree."

Comment.value: if PC is Lord of Keep

value.0: "My <lord/lady>, there can be no charge for you. It was a privilege and an honor to have you stay here."
"And do you think your gold is any good here now? I think not. The good deed you did for Gelani must be rewarded."
"The room is free and I will keep it open for you special, in case you change your mind and want to come and visit again."
"It was the least I could do. Thank you so much for being a guest here at the Mossy Tree."
"Good <quarterday> to you, good <master/mistress>. I am Mr. Mossy and I am very pleased to meet you. How may I be of assistance?"
"You be taking care of yourself now. Evil days are afoot, don't you know."
"It is a lucky thing that I am just full of answers too. Or full of something, according to Gelani. What would you like to know?"
"Is there anything else you be needing, <master/mistress>?"
"I know precious little about politics, I fear. You would be better served speaking to Gelani, since she was once the guildmaster of the merchants guild."
"I know precious little about politics. Go speak to Gelani in the guild office, I am sure she'll be voting for you."
"I know precious little about politics, and since Gelani was murdered, I care even less."
"Let's talk about some more pleasing subject, shall we?"
"I love most of the people of the keep as my own children, though there are a few exceptions. What do you want to know?"
"And what other quandaries might be stuck in your mind that I could help you with?"
"Big... ugly... nasty... that's about all I know. Sorry."
"Right here, of course. The Mossy Tree be the finest inn in the keep."
"Yenna carries magical equipment in her tower. I always was fascinated with her magic, there being so few mages who ever visit the keep."
"I know that Serah at the landowners guild has had some problems, you might be wanting to speak to her."
"Gelani and I get along fine, all rumors to the contrary. She be a fine woman and she was a good guildmaster too, until that god forsaken Thaddeus ruined her name."
"I would love to talk about anything you have a mind for."
"Gelani was once the guildmaster of the merchants guild, until the black-hearted Thaddeus decided he wanted the job. He started rumors about Gelani, backed by his twisted friend, Sir Becket."
"Even though the rumors weren't true, enough people believed them to oust her from her position."
"When everyone turned on her, Gelani just sort of gave up hope. Ah, it was a sad day. I wish someone would help her out, but she says it be none of my business. Any other questions?"
"T'is a terrible thing he did and I sure wish someone would help her get her life back in order. But she tells me it is none of my business, so we should talk about something else."
"You helped the dear soul get her life back in order and I cannot thank you enough for it."
"They found the poor dear's body in a dark alley... I... I will sorely miss her. She was a good friend and a good partner."
"Nay, must have been some thief in the night, for she had no possessions on her when they found the body."
"Then you have come to the right place, and I don't mind saying that you have excellent taste, good <master/mistress>."
"Now some folk like to spend their hard earned wages staying at the Silver Lily, and I'm not one to say anything bad about Mr. Garrot..."
"Oh, now look at me rambling on now. Gelani would have had my tongue in the old days. Now let me think... ah yes, a room. We do happen to have one available. The cost is 15 gold for a week."

Comment.value: take 15 gold, unlock door to pc room, indefinitely.

value.0: "Good enough. I will have someone around to unlock the door. Just come see me when you are ready to leave so we can settle up the bill."

LinkComment.value: If PC was nice to Dylan and he told them this.

value.0: "Ah, there be one thing Mr. Mossy never jests about with a customer and that be gold. With the monsters invading the lands, the inn is brimming almost full with refugees and the like."
"Ah, so you be the one. I'll tell you what, give me ten gold now and I'll charge ten for every week after that to an account. You can settle up when you are ready to move on, agreed?"
"Very well then. Was there anything else I could be doing for you?"
"Well, you can rest here in the common room for now, if you have to. Can't promise you won't get pick pocketed though... or landed on in a bar brawl. We've had a more unsavory crowd lately."
"I'll be having the door unlocked for you then. Just keep using it and come back to see me when you are ready to leave."
"Be there anything else I can do for you?"
"But you already have a room, good <master/mistress>. If you really want to pay for it again, you are more than welcome to, but why waste your gold?"
"I am here to settle my account."
"I can't pay it."
"If you really feel that way, shouldn't the room be free?"
"Thank you."
"Here you go."
"Thank you."
"Goodbye."
"I have some questions for you."
"That's all my questions."
"What do you know about the election?"
"I have questions about the keep."
"That's all my questions about the keep."
"What do you know about the Masked Man's forces?"
"Where can I get a room?"
"Where can I get equipment?"
"Where can I find employment?"
"Tell me about Gelani."
"Let's talk about something else."
"What do you mean?"
